Earlier this month, smartphone maker vivo became the latest Chinese tech company to face scrutiny in India. Similar investigations also happened to Xiaomi, OPPO, and Huawei. In fact, Chinese companies are not the only foreign investors facing difficulties in India. The Chinese embassy in India warned that India's frequent investigations would impede the improvement of the country's business environment by hurting foreign business confidence. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng argues that hurting foreign brands won't help India's development.